<br>
I'd say a combination of A note, 1 charged item, 1 word and 1 rune all together in the 4-slots perhaps? The way the quest is written, it seems all 3 of them have theories on the path, but more than likely a combination of all 3 must be used to get the final goal.<br>
<br>
Ok, let's go back to the 4 items again.<br>
<br>
Amulet of Knowledge, with 5 charges of Shade.<br>
Book of Forgotten Magic, with 5 charges Group Resist Magic<br>
Arcane quill, with 5 charges of Elemental Armor.<br>
Gem of Flowing Breath, with 5 charges of EB<br>
<br>
Shade=Enchanter (39)<br>
Elemental armor = Wiz/mag (44)<br>
GRM=Enchanter (49)<br>
EB= Enchanter (12)<br>
<br>
Ok, so I thought I was on to something for a minute until the EB spell was level 12. And everlasting breath is 51, so not much better because there are no 51 words/runes. I'll have to double-check now to see if it is enduring or everlasting on the item. Everyone just keeps saying &quot;EB&quot;.<br>
<br>
My thought was combine atttempts with the charged item and the spell research Runes &amp; words of the same level. So the book with Grm + words of bondage + rune of concussion for example, then toss in Note A (or C) to have 4 items.<br>
